    <edge source="marie_curie:chunk1" target="Nobel Prize in Physics">
      <data key="d15">["MENTIONS"]</data>
      <data key="d16">1</data>
      <data key="d17">["Nobel Prize in Physics along with Pierre Curie and Henri Becquerel for their work on radioactivity.\n\nIn 1911, she won a second Nobel Prize, this time in Chemistry, for her discovery of radium and polonium. She founded the Curie Institutes in Paris and Warsaw, which remain major medical research centers today.\n\nMarie Curie died in 1934 in Passy, France from aplastic anemia, likely caused by her long-term exposure to radiation."]</data>
    </edge>
